Alan Thicke, the Canadian actor best known for his leading role in the 1980s sitcom &#8220;Growing Pains&#8221; as well as being the father of singer Robin Thicke, has died, a source close to the family said on Tuesday. He was 69.The Los Angeles Times, quoting Robin Thicke&#8217;s publicist, said the actor died of a heart attack.More recently Thicke was set to appear in &#8220;Fuller House,&#8221; a remake of the popular 1990s family sitcom.&#8220;Season 2 Fuller House looking good. I even like the ones I&#8217;m not in!&#8221; Thicke said in a tweet earlier on Tuesday.-Reuters